1
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:17,000
Beautiful evening and gracious breezes

2
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:28,000
that erase from the day

3
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:34,000
excessive and great heat

4
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:41,000
Blow even more calmly,

5
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:48,000
grant our wishes

6
00:20:48,000 --> 00:21:01,000
Cheer our hearts

7
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:07,000
And sir, do we understand each other?

8
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:11,000
Yes sir, everything understood

9
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:18,000
There's no need to speak anymore

10
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:23,000
He leaves without saying goodbye...

11
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:26,000
Where could my beloved be?

12
00:22:26,000 --> 00:22:33,000
I'm starting to suspect

13
00:22:39,500 --> 00:22:54,500
Heaven conspires to my design

14
00:22:54,500 --> 00:23:05,500
Beautiful prospect, I'm committed with good judgment to its triumph

15
00:23:12,500 --> 00:23:18,500
Ah father, being such to me, you love me

16
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:26,000
Come on, tell me the rest for goodness sake

17
00:23:26,440 --> 00:23:31,000
It's my time

18
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:45,000
It's my time and there's nothing more to be done

19
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:50,000
Ah father, Ah father

20
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:57,000
Speak I beg you

21
00:24:21,200 --> 00:24:27,000
Now, my daughter, it's best to stay silent

22
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:35,000
Secret discussions dont always remain so

23
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:42,000
Do you understand, do you get my meaning?

24
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:54,000
I dare not speak

25
00:25:17,000 --> 00:25:27,000
Now, my daughter, it's best to stay silent, I dare not speak

26
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:30,000
You get my meaning, I dare not speak

27
00:25:30,000 --> 00:25:37,000
Truly, it would be a great incivility

28
00:25:37,000 --> 00:25:44,000
to deprive you of comfort and freedom

29
00:25:45,000 --> 00:25:50,000
Let's go, brother, let's go

30
00:25:50,000 --> 00:26:02,000
Let's go sister, to dine for now

31
00:26:41,000 --> 00:26:49,000
Each one keeps their agreement, everyone

32
00:26:49,000 --> 00:26:56,000
We may see each other with the passing of time

33
00:27:01,000 --> 00:27:15,000
We can happily converse among ourselves

34
00:28:13,000 --> 00:28:18,000
Yes, daughter, in the end I've found you a husband

35
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:20,000
And when?

36
00:28:20,000 --> 00:28:22,000
Now, the deal is concluded

37
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:24,000
With Nanni?

38
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:27,000
Oh, Nanni indeed! He can wipe that drool off his chin

39
00:28:27,000 --> 00:28:31,000
This time, he won't get any

40
00:28:31,000 --> 00:28:33,000
But...

41
00:28:33,000 --> 00:28:39,000
There aren't many 'buts', my daughter, Nanni is poor

42
00:28:39,000 --> 00:28:41,000
And I who am rich?

43
00:28:41,000 --> 00:28:43,000
You will be

44
00:28:43,000 --> 00:28:49,000
What does it matter if I'll be rich, if I won't be happy?

45
00:28:49,800 --> 00:28:51,000
And why not?

46
00:28:51,000 --> 00:28:54,400
Because I love him

47
00:28:54,400 --> 00:29:00,400
You make me laugh. Now, you'll love this one

48
00:29:00,400 --> 00:29:06,400
But how can one love another, when one turns from their beloved?

49
00:29:06,400 --> 00:29:09,400
Easily, girls don't have a will of their own

50
00:29:11,400 --> 00:29:14,000
But when it comes from within, what can be done?

51
00:29:14,000 --> 00:29:16,600
One obeys and stays silent

52
00:29:17,900 --> 00:29:24,200
But what should I do, if Nanni comes with such charm?

53
00:29:24,200 --> 00:29:28,200
Turn your back to him, and walk away

54
00:29:49,200 --> 00:30:08,200
When he comes to make love, you must always tell him no

55
00:30:09,200 --> 00:30:12,200
Do you care for me?

56
00:30:12,200 --> 00:30:16,200
No, sir

57
00:30:16,200 --> 00:30:18,200
Sir, no

58
00:30:21,200 --> 00:30:23,200
Do you want to marry me?

59
00:30:23,200 --> 00:30:25,700
Sir, no

60
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:32,320
I know well what I'm doing

61
00:30:34,500 --> 00:30:38,000
I'm your father,

62
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:42,000
and this is my wish

63
00:30:50,000 --> 00:30:52,900
Beware of saying yes to him

64
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:27,000
Poor me! Poor Nanni!

65
00:31:27,700 --> 00:31:37,000
How can I keep saying no to him when I always want to say yes?

66
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:41,000
He cares for me so much!

67
00:31:41,500 --> 00:31:45,000
We've been bonded in love for so long,

68
00:31:45,000 --> 00:31:48,000
and to leave him like this...

69
00:31:49,100 --> 00:31:52,000
breaks my heart

70
00:31:53,000 --> 00:31:58,000
Yet, I must obey and so perish

71
00:31:58,000 --> 00:32:00,000
For Heaven's sake!

72
00:32:01,000 --> 00:32:06,000
There he is; it might be better if I leave

73
00:32:06,000 --> 00:32:09,000
Where are you going, Sandrina?

74
00:32:09,000 --> 00:32:11,500
I don't even know myself

75
00:32:12,000 --> 00:32:13,000
Are you perchance angry?

76
00:32:13,000 --> 00:32:15,000
No!

77
00:32:15,000 --> 00:32:17,000
But, you seem troubled

78
00:32:17,000 --> 00:32:19,000
Your eyes are red

79
00:32:19,000 --> 00:32:23,000
You look like you've been crying

80
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:27,000
Tell me, dear, what happened?

81
00:32:27,000 --> 00:32:29,000
Nothing

82
00:32:29,000 --> 00:32:31,400
But why won't you look at me?

83
00:32:31,400 --> 00:32:33,900
Why won't you speak to me?

84
00:32:33,900 --> 00:32:36,900
Because... no

85
00:32:37,000 --> 00:32:40,500
What? What have I done?

86
00:32:40,500 --> 00:32:42,500
I don't know...

87
00:32:42,500 --> 00:32:46,500
Poor me! What does this mean?

88
00:32:46,500 --> 00:32:53,500
Is it that you do not care for me anymore? That you share no more love for me?

89
00:32:53,500 --> 00:32:57,500
(And yet I must say it) No, sir

90
00:32:58,000 --> 00:33:05,500
What? Am I not the one you've loved until now, the one who loved you faithfully?

91
00:33:05,500 --> 00:33:07,500
The one who was to marry you?

92
00:33:07,500 --> 00:33:09,500
No, sir

93
00:33:09,500 --> 00:33:14,000
You speak to me this way, and yet you cry?

94
00:33:14,000 --> 00:33:21,500
Black soul! Deceitful, wicked girl, you wish for my downfall, you desire my death

95
00:33:22,000 --> 00:33:26,000
You'll be pleased. I'll go drown myself in some ditch

96
00:33:26,000 --> 00:33:29,000
or from some cliff, I'll go and break my neck

97
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:36,000
With such a thorn in my heart, I can't go on living

98
00:33:36,000 --> 00:33:38,560
Ah no, sir!

99
00:33:41,560 --> 00:33:45,560
But why do you hold me back? What do you care about me?

100
00:33:45,560 --> 00:33:49,000
You don't send me away? Does this heart not betray me?

101
00:33:49,560 --> 00:33:51,560
You won't leave me, cruel one?

102
00:33:51,560 --> 00:33:53,560
No, sir

103
00:33:53,560 --> 00:33:57,560
I'm going mad. Who taught you such an air?

104
00:33:57,560 --> 00:34:01,000
(Truly, it's better if I go away.)

105
00:34:01,700 --> 00:34:03,000
You're leaving?

106
00:34:03,000 --> 00:34:03,600
No

107
00:34:03,600 --> 00:34:06,000
Are you driving me away? Should I leave you?

108
00:34:06,000 --> 00:34:06,700
No

109
00:34:06,700 --> 00:34:08,400
Are you disgusted?

110
00:34:08,400 --> 00:34:09,400
No

111
00:34:09,400 --> 00:34:11,000
Cursed 'no'!

112
00:34:11,000 --> 00:34:13,000
(I'm desperate.)

113
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:19,000
But speak, but talk, finally decide

114
00:34:19,000 --> 00:34:26,000
Do you love me or not? Should I leave or stay?

115
00:34:26,000 --> 00:34:30,000
Am I to be your husband or not?

116
00:34:39,000 --> 00:34:44,000
What a tangled web this is!

117
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:47,000
What do you want me to say? What do you want me to do?

118
00:34:47,000 --> 00:34:55,000
My hostile father scolds and threatens me if I speak of loving you, if I say yes

119
00:34:58,000 --> 00:35:09,000
He commands and tells me he found a husband, that I mustn't oppose, that it's a better match

120
00:35:15,000 --> 00:35:21,000
I must leave you; I can't speak to you

121
00:35:21,000 --> 00:35:23,000
I mustn't oppose

122
00:35:27,000 --> 00:35:29,000
No, I mustn't...

123
00:35:52,000 --> 00:36:00,000
What a tangled web this is!

124
00:36:01,000 --> 00:36:06,000
I must leave you; I can't speak to you

125
00:36:06,000 --> 00:36:14,000
And I'm dying of distress. Is this enough for you?

126
00:37:32,180 --> 00:37:34,180
Now I understand what is going on

127
00:37:35,180 --> 00:37:43,180
That baboon, that raging old sorcerer, has orchestrated this farce at my expense

128
00:37:44,180 --> 00:37:53,180
But I'll see for myself. I want to know who dares to take the bread from my mouth

129
00:37:56,180 --> 00:38:04,180
Sandra is mine. Without her, I couldn't live

130
00:38:06,060 --> 00:38:08,060
Poor Nanni!

131
00:38:08,700 --> 00:38:13,000
It's been more than three years that I've been courting her

132
00:38:13,000 --> 00:38:19,000
Every day, I bring her fruits or a small bouquet

133
00:38:19,000 --> 00:38:28,000
And every night, I serenade her under her window with my little guitar

134
00:38:31,060 --> 00:38:35,060
Is another dandy, who besides is unknown to me,

135
00:38:35,060 --> 00:38:39,060
coming to mess up my plans?

136
00:38:40,580 --> 00:38:44,580
I want to go to her father, I want to know who he is

137
00:38:44,580 --> 00:38:48,580
I want him to tell me everything, from A to Z

138
00:38:49,660 --> 00:39:01,660
And once he's revealed the whole mystery to me, one of us is bound for the cemetery

139
00:39:16,580 --> 00:39:31,580
There's no remedy, no compensation

140
00:39:31,580 --> 00:39:35,580
I feel a gnawing when I think of it

141
00:39:35,580 --> 00:39:39,580
I'm all bile, all poison

142
00:39:39,580 --> 00:39:44,580
My insides burn, my chest is on fire

143
00:39:44,860 --> 00:39:49,860
Before losing her, I'd rather die

144
00:41:45,420 --> 00:41:47,420
That old coot, that sorcerer,

145
00:41:47,420 --> 00:41:50,420
who is nothing but bones and skin,

146
00:41:50,420 --> 00:41:54,420
will regret it, and will swing for it

147
00:45:07,660 --> 00:45:15,660
Here's my dinner ready: spring water, a bit of salad, and Moroccan bread

148
00:45:15,660 --> 00:45:18,660
It's a meal fit for a king

149
00:45:20,300 --> 00:45:24,300
But kings don't have to make their meals tasty

150
00:45:24,300 --> 00:45:29,300
the salsa of fasting and labor

151
00:45:30,740 --> 00:45:35,740
Goodness! It's already night,
and Nencio hasn't come yet

152
00:45:35,740 --> 00:45:43,740
I wouldn't want the devil to stick in his hoof and lead him astray

153
00:45:45,220 --> 00:45:49,220
He hasn't shown up all day

154
00:45:49,220 --> 00:45:59,220
Tonight, I noticed him all troubled and flustered, responding with stammers, and grimacing

155
00:46:01,580 --> 00:46:04,580
Why am I so poor?

156
00:46:04,580 --> 00:46:08,000
Why is he rich and has some stake under the sun?

157
00:46:08,000 --> 00:46:11,000
Everyone envies me, everyone wants him

158
00:46:12,000 --> 00:46:19,000
If he had nothing, I'd have no rivals, and I'd be happier

159
00:46:21,700 --> 00:46:23,700
But I hear someone. Here he is

160
00:46:26,060 --> 00:46:28,060
Ah, it's not him...

161
00:46:29,060 --> 00:46:34,060
It's my Nanni, returning distraught and weary

162
00:46:34,580 --> 00:46:37,000
What the devil is happening?

163
00:46:42,780 --> 00:46:46,080
I'm desperate

164
00:46:46,780 --> 00:46:49,780
I have a demon in my hair

165
00:46:49,780 --> 00:46:54,780
I want to jump off a cliff

166
00:46:54,780 --> 00:46:56,780
Speak. What is it, brother?

167
00:46:56,780 --> 00:47:03,780
Ah, you make me tremble!

168
00:47:03,780 --> 00:47:05,780
What has happened?

169
00:47:05,780 --> 00:47:08,780
Speak, what is it, brother?

170
00:47:08,780 --> 00:47:11,780
N: I'm ruined
V: How? Why?

171
00:47:11,780 --> 00:47:16,780
My Sandrina is not for me

172
00:47:16,780 --> 00:47:18,780
Who has slighted you such?

173
00:47:18,780 --> 00:47:20,780
Your Nencio is taking her from me

174
00:47:20,780 --> 00:47:22,780
My Nencio? Really?

175
00:47:23,000 --> 00:47:30,000
Oh what anger, oh what torment!

176
00:47:30,000 --> 00:47:36,000
I feel my heart pounding,

177
00:47:36,060 --> 00:47:40,060
It cannot end like this

178
00:48:22,580 --> 00:48:25,500
And where is that traitor?

179
00:48:26,300 --> 00:48:30,000
With Sandrina, making love

180
00:48:30,000 --> 00:48:32,000
With Sandrina? Speak, speak!

181
00:48:35,000 --> 00:48:36,000
That traitor...

182
00:48:42,380 --> 00:48:44,980
Ah, you make me tremble

183
00:50:04,300 --> 00:50:10,300
Hurry, hurry, hurry,
let's go find them

184
00:50:13,140 --> 00:50:38,140
I want to tear out his heart,
I want to gut him

185
00:50:45,780 --> 00:50:47,780
[Applause]

186
00:51:57,380 --> 00:51:59,380
[Music]

187
01:03:21,140 --> 01:03:24,140
What will you do with so much clothes on,

188
01:03:25,000 --> 01:03:29,640
It looks like you've raided a Haberdashery?

189
01:03:30,380 --> 01:03:35,580
Oh brother, last night I did not act as you did,

190
01:03:35,580 --> 01:03:39,000
who made such a ruckus,

191
01:03:39,200 --> 01:03:43,000
And then slept soundly like a rock

192
01:03:43,300 --> 01:03:45,300
I haven't slept a wink

193
01:03:45,620 --> 01:03:50,000
And before dawn, I wandered hither and thither,

194
01:03:50,000 --> 01:03:54,000
and have made it so that, unless the devil intervenes,

195
01:03:54,000 --> 01:03:58,100
I hope to thwart the wedding

196
01:03:58,100 --> 01:04:03,100
Well, you know, the early bird catches the worm

197
01:04:03,100 --> 01:04:07,100
Anyway, you're a remarkable woman if you succeed

198
01:04:07,100 --> 01:04:12,000
Do you think Filippa might recognize me?

199
01:04:12,000 --> 01:04:14,000
Not in the slightest

200
01:04:14,000 --> 01:04:16,000
Does this fit me well?

201
01:04:16,000 --> 01:04:22,500
Enchantingly, in these clothes you look just like an eighty-year-old woman

202
01:04:23,000 --> 01:04:25,000
And with the other outfit?

203
01:04:28,060 --> 01:04:29,520
In that one, well...

204
01:04:29,520 --> 01:04:35,900
Trying to turn a woman into a man seems a bit ridiculous to me,

205
01:04:36,300 --> 01:04:41,000
And you might lack some... appendages

206
01:04:41,000 --> 01:04:44,440
Quiet, I hear people. It's time

207
01:04:44,440 --> 01:04:48,440
Be careful. Retreat!

208
01:04:48,440 --> 01:04:50,440
Right Away

209
01:04:50,440 --> 01:04:52,440
Now for the moment of truth

210
01:04:53,000 --> 01:04:54,440
Hurry up

211
01:04:54,440 --> 01:04:57,200
I'm coming, where are we going?

212
01:04:57,200 --> 01:05:01,200
To the judge to file a complaint against that scoundrel Nanni

213
01:05:01,900 --> 01:05:04,200
Oh, dear father...

214
01:05:05,200 --> 01:05:08,200
All aflutter, you'll soon see,

215
01:05:08,200 --> 01:05:10,200
that if the notary wishes to examine me,

216
01:05:10,200 --> 01:05:14,200
I'll start shaking like a leaf

217
01:05:14,200 --> 01:05:19,200
Shake, quiver, crumble,
You've got to go

218
01:05:20,200 --> 01:05:22,920
Pray, sir, may I inquire,

219
01:05:22,920 --> 01:05:27,920
is a certain Nencio the lout residing here?

220
01:05:27,920 --> 01:05:29,400
No, sister

221
01:05:29,400 --> 01:05:33,600
Alas, just my luck!

222
01:05:33,600 --> 01:05:35,800
I must have taken the wrong path

223
01:05:35,800 --> 01:05:39,600
I've been walking for four hours, sir,

224
01:05:39,600 --> 01:05:46,360
searching, asking, inquiring, questioning, and I can't find him...

225
01:05:46,700 --> 01:05:50,120
I believe I've traversed the whole plain

226
01:05:50,120 --> 01:05:53,560
I'll show you the way; he's not far

227
01:05:53,560 --> 01:05:57,040
Ah, so weary, and at this age,

228
01:05:57,040 --> 01:05:59,040
unfortunately, it will be far the same

229
01:05:59,040 --> 01:06:00,940
There it is

230
01:06:00,940 --> 01:06:03,400
May heaven reward you

231
01:06:04,000 --> 01:06:07,000
Oh brother, you're a lifesaver

232
01:06:07,140 --> 01:06:15,140
If you only knew the trouble I'm in because of that man...

233
01:06:16,620 --> 01:06:22,000
"But, one must swallow and remain silent" says the proverb

234
01:06:22,780 --> 01:06:26,780
and "those without judgment better have good legs."

235
01:06:28,580 --> 01:06:31,480
What business do you have with him?

236
01:06:31,700 --> 01:06:36,100
Of that I can't speak, I must remain silent and bite my tongue

237
01:06:37,420 --> 01:06:40,720
S: Poor soul!
F: (She piques my curiosity greatly.)

238
01:06:42,740 --> 01:06:46,400
You can speak freely with me

239
01:06:46,400 --> 01:06:48,400
(That is the husband)

240
01:06:48,400 --> 01:06:49,200
What do you say?!

241
01:06:49,200 --> 01:06:50,800
Oh, nothing

242
01:06:50,800 --> 01:06:57,300
"Once spoken, words don’t return to the mouth," says the proverb

243
01:06:57,300 --> 01:07:01,300
"and he who doesn’t know how to stay silent doesn’t know how to live," I know

244
01:07:01,460 --> 01:07:05,120
I'm not a gossip, except of good recipes!

245
01:07:05,120 --> 01:07:09,880
But those with great troubles, make a loud cry

246
01:07:11,020 --> 01:07:15,020
Speak on, there's no risk in venting to me

247
01:07:18,020 --> 01:07:22,620
I tear up when I think of it

248
01:07:23,460 --> 01:07:25,460
Poor dear daughter!

249
01:07:25,740 --> 01:07:27,740
Poor creatures!

250
01:07:30,700 --> 01:07:34,700
You still have, from what I see, a daughter:

251
01:07:34,940 --> 01:07:36,940
May heaven preserve her for you

252
01:07:37,860 --> 01:07:42,860
She is tall and beautiful, modest, and domestic

253
01:07:43,260 --> 01:07:46,720
Open your eyes, poor wretched woman

254
01:07:47,420 --> 01:07:51,420
Don't drown here like I have done

255
01:07:52,380 --> 01:07:54,380
She was just like you, my dear girl,

256
01:07:55,100 --> 01:07:58,800
Wise and beautiful, and throughout the neighborhood

257
01:07:59,260 --> 01:08:04,040
everyone marvelled at her so much, it was pure joy

258
01:08:05,000 --> 01:08:09,500
"As long as you have teeth in your mouth, you don't know what's in store for you,"

259
01:08:09,940 --> 01:08:11,940
says the proverb

260
01:08:12,620 --> 01:08:17,000
"Those who do nothing make no mistakes, but the truth always floats to the surface,"

261
01:08:18,220 --> 01:08:20,220
And what happened to her?

262
01:08:21,260 --> 01:08:23,260
This Nencio, on Carnival, came to Peregola

263
01:08:25,820 --> 01:08:27,820
He saw her and became infatuated

264
01:08:28,540 --> 01:08:32,240
Everyone said he was such a good match

265
01:08:32,500 --> 01:08:34,500
and the girl let herself be charmed

266
01:08:36,420 --> 01:08:41,420
The fire ignited, and the devil fiercely fanned the flames,

267
01:08:41,780 --> 01:08:45,000
that they secretly wed in haste

268
01:08:46,740 --> 01:08:50,050
(Nencio married! Oh, the rascal!)

269
01:08:51,060 --> 01:08:53,060
For a while, he played the good husband

270
01:08:53,060 --> 01:08:57,990
Gradually, he grew distant, until he completely pulled away

271
01:08:59,300 --> 01:09:05,120
Now, brother, it's been three days since he's shown himself,

272
01:09:05,120 --> 01:09:09,200
and he's left her without bread, without meat,

273
01:09:09,200 --> 01:09:16,500
alone in bed with two children in the cradle, and one at her breast

274
01:09:18,060 --> 01:09:22,200
S: My God, what a scoundrel! And you wanted...
F: Quiet!

275
01:09:22,580 --> 01:09:28,700
Just imagine how she manages nursing that poor child

276
01:09:33,160 --> 01:09:38,400
"The barrel gives the wine it has," says the proverb

277
01:09:38,400 --> 01:09:40,400
"To feed on anger is to drink of poison,"

278
01:09:40,900 --> 01:09:44,000
sleep eludes, even with poppy's aid,

279
01:09:44,000 --> 01:09:46,000
when filled with such deep sorrow and quiet pain

280
01:09:47,540 --> 01:09:49,540
Oh, what a scoundrel!

281
01:09:49,820 --> 01:09:51,820
You should seek justice, madam

282
01:09:52,260 --> 01:09:56,800
I hope to bring him around, if possible, through reason

283
01:09:56,860 --> 01:09:58,860
This rogue deserves no mercy

284
01:10:00,460 --> 01:10:05,160
Ah, brother, legal disputes and courts are not for me

285
01:10:06,300 --> 01:10:11,300
"Money and friendship break justice's neck,"

286
01:10:11,300 --> 01:10:13,300
says the proverb...

287
01:10:14,900 --> 01:10:18,240
"and he who dosen't 'grease the weal' is always wrong."

288
01:10:19,660 --> 01:10:27,660
And then there are hearings, mandates, appeals, citations, contradictions, examinations, and witnesses

289
01:10:27,820 --> 01:10:34,000
My dear brother, it never ends...

290
01:10:35,380 --> 01:10:42,800
And I am old, and full of woes

291
01:11:19,180 --> 01:11:32,180
I have a tumor in my knee
that forces me to limp

292
01:11:38,260 --> 01:11:51,960
I have a fistula in this eye
that always makes me tear up

293
01:11:51,960 --> 01:12:01,000
I have a cough that's killing me,

294
01:12:01,500 --> 01:12:15,300
And I struggle to breathe

295
01:12:34,900 --> 01:12:36,900
That poor girl...

296
01:12:39,660 --> 01:12:44,920
She's on the verge of fading away

297
01:12:47,340 --> 01:12:54,800
Ah, what will become of me?

298
01:12:55,100 --> 01:13:11,110
If on top of so many woes, I had to face litigation

299
01:13:49,460 --> 01:14:03,460
I have a tumor in my knee
that forces me to limp

300
01:16:10,220 --> 01:16:11,900
Che ne dite ?
What do you think?

301
01:16:11,900 --> 01:16:13,900
Ah, my child, I've nearly lost my mind

302
01:16:14,860 --> 01:16:19,000
If Nencio has a wife, he can't marry me?

303
01:16:19,420 --> 01:16:21,420
We'll send him to marry the pillory

304
01:16:21,740 --> 01:16:27,000
Scoundrel! Rogue! Woe to him if he comes before me

305
01:16:28,460 --> 01:16:30,460
Yet you say he's rich...?

306
01:16:32,300 --> 01:16:39,440
Oh, perhaps riches are a privilege for those with wicked inclinations to become scoundrels

307
01:16:40,380 --> 01:16:42,380
So, it's better to be poor?

308
01:16:43,180 --> 01:16:45,180
Certainly

309
01:16:45,420 --> 01:16:48,280
Better to be miserable than wicked

310
01:16:49,180 --> 01:16:55,480
Ah, if the devil brings him to me again, I don't know what I'll do with that unworthy

311
01:16:55,900 --> 01:16:57,900
S: There he is!
F: We'd better avoid the confrontation

312
01:17:00,980 --> 01:17:05,890
Hey Filippo! Sandrina! Don't shut the door, listen!

313
01:17:08,260 --> 01:17:10,260
What's the meaning of this fine courtesy?

314
01:17:10,540 --> 01:17:14,480
They surely saw me and know the reason I'm tracking them down,

315
01:17:14,480 --> 01:17:17,120
