Everything is now clear to me

386
01:27:18,500 --> 01:27:21,800
Now I understand Filippo's departure

387
01:27:22,580 --> 01:27:24,580
He has found a better match

388
01:27:25,220 --> 01:27:28,520
And to not appear as a turncoat or crazy,

389
01:27:28,520 --> 01:27:32,000
he made up that excuse and harrasses me

390
01:27:32,800 --> 01:27:34,800
But I will set things right

391
01:27:36,200 --> 01:27:38,500
I no longer care about that foolish girl

392
01:27:39,000 --> 01:27:45,420
For me, it's over, but I want to at least tell her bluntly my side of the story

393
01:27:45,420 --> 01:27:48,180
To show her that I can sing as well

394
01:27:50,060 --> 01:27:52,540
I don't care about that gossip

395
01:27:52,540 --> 01:27:54,540
But I don't want to be painted as ridiculous

396
01:27:54,820 --> 01:27:56,820
I want things to proceed orderly

397
01:27:57,100 --> 01:27:59,800
I don't want to be dominated

398
01:28:00,500 --> 01:28:06,080
I'm not worried. There's no real danger in returning to argue with old men

399
01:28:06,420 --> 01:28:10,240
But I want to talk. I want to vent

400
01:28:10,620 --> 01:28:13,080
At least I will make him learn how to bargain

401
01:28:14,580 --> 01:28:16,580
Gentleman

402
01:28:16,880 --> 01:28:18,300
Most Illustrious

403
01:28:18,300 --> 01:28:19,500
What are you doing?

404
01:28:19,500 --> 01:28:20,500
Nothing, sir

405
01:28:20,500 --> 01:28:24,000
What do you mean nothing? What do you seek from that house?

406
01:28:24,380 --> 01:28:26,380
I was going to speak a word to Filippo

407
01:28:27,180 --> 01:28:28,320
Do you know him?

408
01:28:28,320 --> 01:28:30,320
Of course

409
01:28:30,320 --> 01:28:31,900
And me?

410
01:28:31,900 --> 01:28:34,000
I don't believe I've ever seen you before

411
01:28:35,340 --> 01:28:40,500
Listen here, you clod, and you will know

412
01:28:42,000 --> 01:28:45,840
I am the Marquis of Ripafratta,

413
01:28:45,840 --> 01:28:50,000
who has fiefs, and marquisates, baronies, and principalities,

414
01:28:50,580 --> 01:28:52,580
and who, by the hundreds in nobility,

415
01:28:52,980 --> 01:28:56,500
counts the quarters and measures them by the bushel

416
01:28:56,500 --> 01:28:58,200
Ah, I believe it, Most Illustrious One

417
01:28:58,200 --> 01:28:59,100
That's not all

418
01:28:59,100 --> 01:29:05,550
Know that in my service I have pages, and I have knights, lackys, stable boys, and black capes,

419
01:29:05,550 --> 01:29:09,000
and a world full of beasts and persons,

420
01:29:09,000 --> 01:29:14,320
And that if you ever dare approach this door again...

421
01:29:15,400 --> 01:29:18,760
I will have you beaten to death under a cane

422
01:29:19,100 --> 01:29:21,000
Ah Sir, please don't inconvenience yourself!

423
01:29:21,000 --> 01:29:22,000
Did you understand?

424
01:29:22,000 --> 01:29:23,360
Ah, Most Illustrious, yes

425
01:29:23,360 --> 01:29:24,720
Watch your back

426
01:29:24,720 --> 01:29:26,720
Undoubtedly

427
01:29:27,900 --> 01:29:31,200
But know that Filippo dealt me a nasty slight

428
01:29:31,200 --> 01:29:33,200
What then?

429
01:29:33,200 --> 01:29:38,180
Last night, just last night, he promised me Sandrina's hand

430
01:29:38,550 --> 01:29:42,440
I came this morning to marry her as agreed,

431
01:29:42,440 --> 01:29:45,000
And he chased me away, like a whipped dog

432
01:29:45,000 --> 01:29:48,500
Ah, ah, you make me laugh

433
01:29:48,500 --> 01:29:51,500
Eh, I know that Sandrina is getting married to you today

434
01:29:51,800 --> 01:29:54,480
But I'd like to get even with him

435
01:29:54,700 --> 01:29:55,500
With whom?

436
01:29:55,500 --> 01:29:56,500
With that old man

437
01:29:58,540 --> 01:30:02,680
And you think our marriage is all settled?

438
01:30:03,000 --> 01:30:05,100
Oh, unfortunately, I know

439
01:30:05,100 --> 01:30:17,000
Poor fool. Do you think I'd degrade my many titles, and such lofty and supreme nobility, to marry a mere peasant?

440
01:30:17,100 --> 01:30:19,000
But a certain German servant of yours...

441
01:30:19,000 --> 01:30:21,000
He believes it, and so does Filippo

442
01:30:22,300 --> 01:30:33,300
In fact, for Sandrina I do feel love, so to give her great honor, I'll marry her to my kitchen boy

443
01:30:34,000 --> 01:30:38,040
When drafting the contract, the names will be changed

444
01:30:38,040 --> 01:30:41,960
And one of my servants will step in for the marriage

445
01:30:41,960 --> 01:30:45,700
And she will be a maid at my service

446
01:30:46,740 --> 01:30:50,900
Oh, wonderful! But once Filippo finds out, what will he say?

447
01:30:50,900 --> 01:30:52,560
What do you want him to say?

448
01:30:52,560 --> 01:31:00,560
Sandrina agrees, and once the contract is signed, there's no remedy, and what's done is done

449
01:31:01,300 --> 01:31:02,560
He's going to look so foolish

450
01:31:03,460 --> 01:31:07,480
Oh, how much I'd pay to be present at this wedding!

451
01:31:07,900 --> 01:31:11,600
Come, you can serve as a witness

452
01:31:11,600 --> 01:31:14,500
Ah, please do it, sir, for pity's sake!

453
01:31:14,500 --> 01:31:15,800
Where do you live?

454
01:31:15,800 --> 01:31:17,000
Over there

455
01:31:17,000 --> 01:31:19,000
Go there and wait

456
01:31:19,420 --> 01:31:23,000
I'll send a servant to notify you

457
01:31:23,300 --> 01:31:25,380
I'll go

458
01:31:35,820 --> 01:31:44,960
Oh, what delight!

459
01:31:44,960 --> 01:32:11,000
If I get to see this old man foaming at the mouth, raging, fuming...

460
01:32:11,460 --> 01:32:19,520
The marchioness, the cook, when it's finally revealed...

461
01:32:20,000 --> 01:32:25,520
What yelling, that ashen face

462
01:32:25,520 --> 01:32:30,000
What will that old wizard do?

463
01:32:30,540 --> 01:32:52,000
I believe I'll die of laughter, that I'll burst

464
01:38:21,500 --> 01:38:25,240
Let's spread out this table cloth here

465
01:38:25,240 --> 01:38:30,840
Here, a chair. Here another. A stool. One more here

466
01:38:31,180 --> 01:38:33,320
Alright

467
01:38:33,660 --> 01:38:39,800
Oh my dear, you were born with a silver spoon in your mouth

468
01:38:39,800 --> 01:38:41,800
Indeed, a great fortune!

469
01:38:41,800 --> 01:38:47,100
Oh silly girl. Look at you! You're about to become a great lady

470
01:38:47,100 --> 01:38:51,100
And lose the habit of working and staying healthy

471
01:38:51,100 --> 01:38:55,100
Always traveling by carriage or by palanquin

472
01:38:55,100 --> 01:38:59,700
When one has such good legs, it would feel like being in the pillory

473
01:39:00,860 --> 01:39:04,460
Always dress in fine cloth and velvet

474
01:39:04,460 --> 01:39:06,460
And perhaps suffer more the cold

475
01:39:07,000 --> 01:39:10,900
Have the pleasure of always wearing a pannier

476
01:39:10,900 --> 01:39:17,440
Oh surely, the joy isn't small of banging one's shins in that contraption

477
01:39:17,440 --> 01:39:22,000
Have many persons at your service

478
01:39:22,000 --> 01:39:26,200
And let the public know all one's private business

479
01:39:26,200 --> 01:39:32,000
Have not just a meal on the table every day - but a feast

480
01:39:32,200 --> 01:39:37,800
A great invention, intended to erase one's appetite

645
01:39:37,800 --> 01:39:40,900
Shut it silly girl, or else I'll hit you

646
01:39:42,560 --> 01:39:46,800
But how do you expect me to adapt to becoming a great lady?

647
01:39:46,800 --> 01:39:53,960
What? Do you believe you are the first? Oh my daughter, when fortune provides the rest,

648
01:39:53,960 --> 01:39:58,000
arrogance and folly make their nest

649
01:39:58,500 --> 01:40:00,000
But hush. I hear people

650
01:40:00,980 --> 01:40:07,320
Might it be the Marquis returning with the notary to draft the contract?

651
01:40:07,620 --> 01:40:12,600
Very soon, you'll see what a change of clothes can mean

652
01:40:12,600 --> 01:40:20,240
Oh no! Give me simple bread and onions, and my dear Nanni

653
01:40:52,860 --> 01:40:59,440
Pomp is a great deception

654
01:41:00,260 --> 01:41:17,920
Per un'anima che disprezza il fasto, l'onor, e la ricchezza
For a soul that scorns ostentation, honor, and wealth

655
01:41:18,420 --> 01:42:14,840
I seek not, and I do not desire,
but the peace of my heart

656
01:42:27,880 --> 01:42:44,000
I seek not, and I do not desire,
but the peace of my heart

657
01:44:05,820 --> 01:44:09,090
At your most illustrious service

658
01:44:09,980 --> 01:44:12,000
To whom do you speak?

659
01:44:12,000 --> 01:44:14,000
With you, don't you see?

660
01:44:14,980 --> 01:44:20,000
My master has sent me here with the notary

661
01:44:20,580 --> 01:44:24,320
to draft his marriage contract

662
01:44:25,000 --> 01:44:29,320
And he told me to bring a witness

663
01:44:30,300 --> 01:44:32,620
Oh wonderful, how delightful!

664
01:44:33,500 --> 01:44:35,520
And the Marquis?

665
01:44:35,700 --> 01:44:38,240
Shouldn't he be present for this?

666
01:44:41,060 --> 01:44:45,700
He will come to sign the contract

667
01:44:45,700 --> 01:45:00,000
He has now gone to make arrangements for the departure, the dresses for the bride, the ceremonial carriages, and everything besides

668
01:45:00,800 --> 01:45:05,000
Ah, my dear daughter, what great fortune is this?

669
