685
01:47:34,700 --> 01:47:39,480
Così promettono, così si sposano
Thusly they vow, thusly they wed
686
01:47:39,480 --> 01:47:44,400
not constraining and obligating themselves

687
01:47:44,700 --> 01:47:49,050
This will suffice

688
01:47:49,860 --> 01:47:51,860
Let them sign

689
01:47:51,980 --> 01:47:53,980
Where?

690
01:47:55,200 --> 01:47:59,480
Right here the witnesses

691
01:47:59,540 --> 01:48:03,880
Here they are

692
01:48:04,580 --> 01:48:06,580
Where is the Marquis?

693
01:48:07,060 --> 01:48:09,060
Where is the groom?

694
01:48:09,380 --> 01:48:18,920
He's arriving now
(It makes me laugh in truth)

695
01:48:19,940 --> 01:48:24,540
But when is he coming?

696
01:48:24,540 --> 01:48:28,640
Here he is

697
01:48:29,860 --> 01:48:31,860
This is my Nanni

698
01:48:31,980 --> 01:48:33,980
This is Vespina

699
01:48:34,420 --> 01:48:38,000
Mi vien da ridere, in verità
It makes me laugh in truth

700
01:48:39,260 --> 01:48:42,560
Che baronata! Che imbroglio è questo?
What a farce! What is this deception?

701
01:48:42,940 --> 01:48:48,640
Thus infidelity is punished

702
01:48:49,100 --> 01:48:52,400
I won't agree to any pact
I know well what I will do

703
01:48:52,740 --> 01:48:56,160
The contract is made and signed, it can no longer be undone

704
01:48:56,300 --> 01:48:58,040
You are my wife
you are my husband

705
01:48:58,060 --> 01:48:59,640
This is finished, and, as so, how it goes

706
01:48:59,900 --> 01:49:03,280
Mister errant one, mister vagabond, leave here at once

707
01:49:03,280 --> 01:49:07,640
Nobody has pity for me in the world

708
01:49:07,640 --> 01:49:09,640
What will become of me?

709
01:49:10,620 --> 01:49:12,300
Listen, scoundrel
710
01:49:12,300 --> 01:49:14,300
You do me great wrong

711
01:49:14,420 --> 01:49:16,420
The wife betrayed

712
01:49:16,420 --> 01:49:18,040
A stale lie

713
01:49:18,040 --> 01:49:19,800
The children abandoned

714
01:49:19,800 --> 01:49:21,560
Inventied slander

715
01:49:21,560 --> 01:49:25,560
Listen! Be quiet!

716
01:49:25,560 --> 01:49:30,480
Now you will actually see what has happened

717
01:49:32,100 --> 01:49:40,700
I pretended to be the old woman who speaks in proverbs

718
01:49:41,060 --> 01:49:45,160
The German servant [invented words]

719
01:49:45,160 --> 01:49:49,600
Enough, it was you, Vespina, with such an uncouth manner

720
01:49:49,600 --> 01:49:51,580
You knew how to trick us

721
01:49:51,580 --> 01:49:53,580
Heaven give me patience
it's is an insolence

722
01:49:53,580 --> 01:49:57,280
But what does one do?

723
01:49:58,300 --> 01:50:03,700
What's done is done

724
01:50:10,940 --> 01:50:15,520
So let us then be cheeful

725
01:50:15,660 --> 01:50:39,600
that in a double wedding today at least we will rejoice

726
01:50:47,980 --> 01:53:34,980
[Applause]

727
